<TITLE> Advisers start talks with BNP faction </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 15 (bdnews24.com)--Five advisers sat with BNP's 'reformist' faction for informal talks Tuesday in the lead-up to dialogue, a BNP leader said. A senior BNP leader, retired lieutenant general Mahbubur Rahman, led the six-member delegation that includes acting secretary general Hafizuddin Ahmed. The midday talks started at state guesthouse Meghna, BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia's adviser ZA Khan told bdnews24.com by phone. Law adviser AF Hassan Ariff, communications adviser Ghulam Quader, foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury, LGRD adviser Anwarul Iqbal and commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman represented the government. Earlier in the day, the leaders of the troubled party held a meeting at former finance minister M Saifur Rahman's Gulshan home and made the decision to join the talks. bd
